1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be2 e5 7. Nb3 Be7 8. O-O
O-O 9. Be3 Be6 10. Qd2 Nbd7 11. a4 Rc8 12. a5 Qc7 13. Rfc1 Nc5 14. Nxc5 dxc5
15. f3 Rfd8 { Gaining a tempo first before pushing ...c4. } 16. Qe1 c4 17. Na4
{ Preventing ...Bc5 and threatening Bb6, so Black's next is more or less forced. }
17... Nd7 { Taking control of the important b6 and c5-squares. } 18. Kh1 Qb8
{ Removing the queen from the vulnerable c7-square. Black has a solid position. His main strategical aim is to exchange the dark-squared bishops or just activate his bishop on e7  (for example with ...h6 and ...Bg5)  . Another active possibility for him is to push ...f5. Another move Black can consider is ...Rc6, further increasing his control over the b6 and c5-squares. }
