1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be2 e5 7. Nb3 Be7 8. g4
{ This is an aggressive attempt, but not a very popular one. } 8... h6
{ Preventing g5 and securing the knight on f6. } 9. Be3 Be6
{ Black plays his normal moves in these structures. The bishop comes to e6 and the knight to d7. The immediate threat is to push ...d5. }
10. Bf3 { Preventing ...d5. } 10... Nbd7
{ Finishing development. Black is ready for counterplay on the queenside. } 11.
Qe2 { With the idea of castling long. } 11... Nb6
{ A strong move. Black intends ...Nc4 to immediately target the ever-important dark-squared bishop. With the knight coming to c4 and then ...b5 Black will have excellent play on the queenside. }
