O-O 9. Qd3 Be6 10. Nd5
{ This is harmless, as now Black can even keep the pair of bishops and take on d5 with the knight. }
10... Nxd5 11. exd5 Bc8
{ With a very comfortable position for Black - if necessary he will secure his queenside with ...a5 and ...b6 and will start typical central and kingside play with ...f5, ...Nd7-f6  (or ...Nd7-e5 in case he pushes ...e4)  and so on. }
