1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be2 e5 7. Nb3 Be7 8. O-O
O-O 9. a4 Be6 10. Bf3 Nbd7 11. Re1 Qb8
{ This is a great idea. Black wants to activate the Be7 via d8. } 12. Be3
{ White tries to hinder Black's idea by intending Qd2 and Rad1, pressurizing d6. }
12... Rc8
{ Since White is ready for Black's bishop transfer Be7-d8, Black makes another useful move by putting the rook on the c-file. The queen is quite comfortable on b8, from where she can support the b-pawn push. }
13. Qd2
{ 13.a5  can be met by the thematic  13...Bd8 !  14.Qd2  b5  15.axb6  Bxb6  with excellent play.   After the text White is ready to push  a5  and play  Red1  , so Black prevents it by  13...b6. }
13... b6
{ Black has good play here. He is harmoniously developed and can further consider the maneuver ...Ra7-c7 and perhaps put the queen on b7. He will always be on the lookout for a possible ...b5. }
