O-O 9. a4 Be6 10. Bf3 Nbd7 11. Re1 Qb8 12. Nd2
{ This allows Black to implement his plan. } 12... Bd8 13. Nf1
{ If White plays a5 then Black responds with ...b5. } 13... Ba5
{ The bishop is very active here, pinning the knight and threatening to take it. }
14. Bd2 Qc7
{ Black has excellent play - he managed to activate the bishop and now he will put a rook on the c-file. He may also consider taking on c3 and playing ...Nc5, attacking the pawn on e4, an idea Vachier-Lagrave has used on a couple of occasions. }
