13. Qd4 { More or less the only move as it prevents ...b4. } 13... Bb7
{ Black is at least equal here. Exchanges on e7 and b3 will ensue when Black will have very good central control. With a strong bishop on b7 he will probably consider the move ...e5, fixing the pawn on e4. }
