1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bc4 e6 7. Bb3 Nbd7 8.
O-O Nc5 9. Re1 Be7 10. f4 O-O 11. e5 dxe5 12. fxe5 Nxb3 13. axb3 Nd5 14. Ne4
{ White tries to keep more pieces on the board, but this runs into Black's next move. }
14... f5
{ A strong move which immediately attacks White's strong centralized knight and liberates Black's play. }
15. exf6 Nxf6 16. Nf2 e5
{ An excellent move, Black sacrifices a pawn in order to open the diagonal for the dormant bishop on c8 and obtains great compensation after 17. Rxe5. }
17. Rxe5 Qc7 { Followed by ...Bd6. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
