1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bc4 e6 7. Bb3 Nbd7 8.
Bg5 Nc5 9. f4 Be7 10. Qf3 Qc7 11. O-O { Castling short is innocuous. } 11...
O-O { Black has secured the king and will push ...b5 next. } 12. f5 b5 13. a3
{ 13.fxe6  fxe6  14.Nf5  Bb7  Black will take on  b3  next and the e6-pawn will no longer need protection. With his good central control thanks to the pawns on  e6  and  d6  Black is slightly better here. }
13... Rb8
{ An important move - Black needs the bishop on c8 to defend e6, so he uses the b-file for the rook with the idea to prepare the ...b4 push. }
14. fxe6 fxe6 15. Nf5 Bd8
{ And White will soon be pushed back by moves like ...b4, ...Nxb3 and ...Kh8. }
