1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bc4 e6 7. Bb3 Nbd7 8. f4
Nc5 9. e5 Nfd7 10. exd6 Nf6 11. Be3 Bxd6 12. Qf3 O-O 13. O-O-O Qc7 14. g4
{ Curiously enough this is a losing mistake ! White is vulnerable on the long h1-a8 diagonal and also on the c-file. Black quickly takes advantage of both after his next move. }
14... b5
{ White cannot take the rook because he loses the queen after ...Bb7 and ...Ra8. }
15. Rhf1 Bb7
{ Finishing development with tempo and liberating the c8-square for the rook. }
16. Qh3 Nxb3+
{ This eliminates the bishop and opens the c-file, again with a tempo. } 17.
axb3 Rac8
{ With the threats of ...Ne4 and ...b4 plus the pair of bishops Black has a winning position. }
