Be6 9. Qd3 b5 10. Bxe6 fxe6
{ These positions where Black's f7-pawn moves to e6 are usually very safe for Black as he has covered the sensitive d5 and f5 squares and has the open f-file as an additional asset. }
11. a4 b4
{ Of course, chasing the knight from c3 is one of the basic ideas in the Sicilian. }
12. Ne2 { Or  12.Na2  Nc6. } 12... O-O
