11. Bf2 Qc7 12. O-O-O Bd7
{ Black finishes development and is ready for  ...b5  , starting his traditional queenside attack. The immediate  12...b5  isn't very good as after  13.Nxc6  Qxc6  14.Be2  with  Bf3  to come Black is somewhat exposed along the long diagonal. }
13. Rg1 b5
{ Black's attack is faster here - he can follow it up with ...Rb8 and then push ...b4. }
14. g4 Rb8 15. Qf3 Qb7
{ The key move - with the threatening presence on the b-file the ...b4 move will be even stronger. Black's initiative is already becoming menacing, he has a clear target on the queenside while White's attack is rather vague with Black's king safely defended in the centre. }
