[SetUp "1"]

1. Qxe2
{ It was better for White to take with the knight, as this allows the typical Sicilian exchange sacrifice. }
1... Rxc3 2. bxc3 Qc7
{ It is important to understand that the exchange sacrifice doesn't lead to a win. It changes the character of the game, and it gives Black easy play. He will now play ...Nb6, .. .O-O, ...Na4, possibly prepare ...a5 and ...b4. White is forced on the defensive with no active possibilities while Black can build up his queenside attack at leisure. }
